# --- [ Artificial Intelligence ] ---

* Artificial Intelligence

- Disciplines such as Biology, Neuroscience and Cognitive Psychology gives us key insights into the inner workings of the brain; and through mimicry we are able to create more advanced artificial brains.

- One such insight is the usage of feature detectors within the brain. Feature detectors are clusters of nerve cells specialized at detecting a given feature, such as horizontal lines or the shapes of faces.

* Kittens Who Can't Perceive Horizontal Lines

- In an experiment a group of kittens were raised in such an environment that they never develop feature detectors for horizontal lines.

.link https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QzkMo45pcUo#t=367 Colin Blakemore: Researching the visual cortex

.image inc/orientation.png 400 313

* The Facial Recognition Area

- In an experiment the facial recognition area of a patient suffering from epilepsy was electrically stimulated to establish its use.
.link https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5Yj3nGv0kn8#t=343 Nancy Kanwisher: A neural portrait of the human mind (watch the talk on YouTube)

* Google's Self-Taught Neural Network

Google connected 16,000 processors into a neural network, mimicking the synaptic connections between nerve cells in the brain. The network contained 1 billion connections in total, which is a hundred thousandth of the number of connections in an adult human brain.

After feeding hundreds of hours of YouTube footage into the neural network it had gained the ability to recognize kittens, without ever being told what a cat or kitten was.

.image inc/cat_detection.jpg 250 288

